column5: RIP Lloyd Brevett.   This guy was a pioneer of what we know as reggae.   Ska music was the theme tune for my generation during the gloomy, recession hit years of Thatcher's Britain.             <iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/2N2TJk32_0Y" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
Simon, I'll join you in the boat with some Skatalites...or English Beat, Specials, early Madness, anytime.  RIP, Lloyd
selecter, fishbone, skaface, villains...man I miss ska
LOL, Hey you, don't watch dat...watch dis...great stuff
Im not familiar, but you could easily see some inspiration on other artists.  RIP  Been doing too much of this lately
Your telling me Rick.....here's another one from yesterday.......i was not to big a fan but again love 'em or loathe 'em...influential.  BEASTIE BOYS STAR DEAD

the Servegera(sp) used to be our home base; one step beyond, the izen brothers, fat cats.. man that was a spompin' good time!!! and the epic after parties ..  I've lost my touch, have not been to a live show in years.
